The paper deals with monitoring problems in distributed data streams, which are typically studied in the areas of data structures (cs.DS) and data mining (cs.DM). The use of randomised algorithms suggests a focus on machine learning and probabilistic methods (cs.LG), while the minimisation of communication implies an interest in information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY).
